        "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes #4078 by updating the deprecated `assert` syntax for import assertions to the new `with` syntax, which is required for Node.js 22+ compatibility.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Updated `rollup.config.js` to use `with` instead of `assert` for JSON import assertion\r\n- Updated `package.json` engines requirement from `>=12` to `>=18.20` to ensure compatibility with the `with` syntax\r\n\r\n## Background\r\n\r\nNode.js 22.0.0 deprecated the `assert` syntax for import assertions. The `with` syntax was introduced in Node.js v18.20 and v20.10 as the replacement. This change ensures D3.js can be built on Node.js 22+.\r\n\r\n## Breaking Change\r\n\r\nThis updates the minimum required Node.js version from 12 to 18.20. Users on older Node.js versions will need to upgrade.- Replace deprecated 'assert' with 'with' syntax in rollup.config.js\r\n- Update minimum Node.js version to >=18.20 in package.json\r\n\r\nFixes #4078",
