        "body": "\r\n add Login page and integrate with backend; add login CTA on Signup\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\nAdds a fully styled Login page to the React/Tailwind frontend and integrates it with the existing backend login API. Also adds a prominent “Log in” button beneath the Signup button so users can switch flows immediately after signup.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n- New `frontend/src/pages/Login.jsx`:\r\n  - Email or Username + Password fields\r\n  - Client-side validation and loading/disabled states\r\n  - API call to `POST http://localhost:3000/api/users/login`\r\n  - Stores `token` in `localStorage` if provided\r\n  - Success/error messaging with fast timeout handling\r\n- Updated `frontend/src/App.jsx`:\r\n  - Toggle between Signup and Login views\r\n- Updated `frontend/src/pages/Signup.jsx`:\r\n  - Full-width \"Log in\" button under the Signup button\r\n\r\n### How to test\r\n1) Backend\r\n   - Ensure `.env` has `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET_KEY`, `JWT_EXPIRES_IN`\r\n   - From `backend/`: `npm run dev`\r\n   - Optional: `GET /api/health` → `{ status: 'ok' }`\r\n\r\n2) Frontend\r\n   - From `frontend/`: `npm run dev`\r\n   - Use the new Log in button on the Signup page to switch\r\n   - Attempt login with a valid user; expect 200 and `localStorage.auth_token` if token is returned\r\n\r\n### Screens\r\n- Signup: centered card with Signup and Log in buttons\r\n- Login: matching aesthetic, email/username support\r\n\r\n### Follow-ups (optional)\r\n- Route-based navigation via React Router (`/login`, `/signup`)\r\n- Per-field error surfacing from backend validation\r\n- Redirect to dashboard/profile after auth success",
